(3) for an observation selected in (2), calculate the decomposition of model prediction using Ceteris paribus / ICE profiles (packages for R: DALEX, ALEPlot, packages for python: AIX360, pyCeterisParibus, PDPbox, own code).¶

In [10]:
def cp_profile(model, X, variable, idx):
    
    def modify_obs(row, var, val):
        row = row.copy()
        row[var] = val
        return row
    
    if not isinstance(idx, Iterable):
        idx = [idx]
    obs = X.iloc[idx]
    
    original_val = obs[variable].copy()
    original_pred = model.predict(obs)

    min_val = np.min(X[variable])
    max_val = np.max(X[variable])
    xs = np.linspace(min_val, max_val, 1000)
    preds = np.array([model.predict(modify_obs(obs, variable, val)) for val in xs])
    #preds = preds.reshape(preds.shape[0], 1)
    
    plt.plot(xs, preds)
    plt.xlabel(variable)
    plt.ylabel("Target")
    
    for (x, y) in zip(original_val.values, original_pred):
        plt.plot([x], [y], marker='o', markersize=4, color="red")
    
    plt.show()

for variable in X_train.columns:
    cp_profile(model, X_train, variable, OBS_IDX)

In [14]:
lgb_train = lgb.Dataset(X_train, y_train)
lgb_eval = lgb.Dataset(X_test, y_test, reference=lgb_train)

params = {
    'boosting_type': 'gbdt',
    'objective': 'regression',
    'metric': {'l2', 'l1'},
    'num_leaves': 31,
    'learning_rate': 0.05,
    'feature_fraction': 0.9,
    'bagging_fraction': 0.8,
    'bagging_freq': 5,
    'verbose': 0
}

gbm = lgb.train(params,
                lgb_train,
                num_boost_round=200,
                valid_sets=lgb_eval,
                early_stopping_rounds=50)

y_pred = gbm.predict(X_test, num_iteration=gbm.best_iteration)
print('The msle of prediction is:', msle(y_test, y_pred))

In [17]:
def shap_plot(model, data, j):
    explainerModel = shap.TreeExplainer(model)
    shap_values_Model = explainerModel.shap_values(data)
    return shap.force_plot(explainerModel.expected_value, shap_values_Model[j], data.iloc[[j]])
shap.initjs()
